Title:

Capital Markets Earnings Call Transcript Summarization Agent

Problem Statement:

Earnings call transcripts contain valuable insights but are lengthy and complex, making it difficult for analysts to quickly grasp key messages. Manual summarization is time-consuming and inconsistent. A generative Al agent that produces concise, thematic summaries highlighting financial performance, risks, and management outlook improves analyst productivity and decision-making.

Data Requirements:

Transcripts of earnings calls in text format. Company financial reports and stock performance data for context. Industry-specific terminology dictionaries. Historical summarized transcripts for reference.

(Feel free to generate synthetic data as well from the provided access)

Expected Output:

The output includes structured text summaries with sections for key financial metrics, management discussion, and analyst questions. Summaries are formatted for analyst reports and support exporting as PDF or DOCX.

Be creative to go beyond as you solve the above needs
